Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches
long and ⅓ inch thick). Halve @potato bun{2}.

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season
generously with salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While carrots roast, heat a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning
too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @tofu{1} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of
#plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until tofu is about
½ inch thick. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Brush tofu all over with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Working one piece at a
time, press tofu into panko mixture until fully coated on both sides.

Heat a ⅓-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in pan used for bacon over medium-high
heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko mixture sizzles when added to
the pan, add coated tofu. Cook until crust is golden brown and tofu is cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Fry in batches if necessary; lower heat if chicken begins to brown too
> quickly.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

AIR FRYER ALTERNATIVE: Coat an #air fryer basket{} with cooking spray;
arrange coated tofu side by side in basket. Coat tops of tofu with cooking
spray. Air fry at 390 degrees for ~{7%minutes}. Flip tofu and coat again with
cooking spray; air fry until cooked through and crispy, ~{7%minutes} more.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
@honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Toast buns until golden brown.

Spread top buns with as much honey mustard mayo as you like. Fill buns with tofu
and bacon.

Divide sandwiches and carrots between plates. Serve with any remaining honey
mustard mayo on the side for dipping.